oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Incidence and Treatment of Abnormal Postpartum Ovarian Function in Dairy Cows
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Archbald, L. F.
Norman, S. N.
Bliss, E. L.
Tran, T.

oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: GnRH
dairy cows
postpartum
ovarian function
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The objectives of this study were to determine 1) the incidence of abnormal postpartum ovarian function in a large dairy herd in North Central Florida and 2) the effectiveness of gonadotrophin releasing hormone (GnRH) in treating this condition. The study was conducted from April 1988 to June 1989.
